wiki.summary: “Mad Love” is the second single off Mabel’s album, High Expectations. It talks about a sexual relationship between two people. On her YouTube channel, the singer talked about the creative process behind the song-writing in the studio session after the set of artists had written the previous single: I just wanna write something positive that had attitude, but still was sending quite a simple message of just how good it feels when you like somebody and they like you, and sometimes it doesn’t have to be more complicated than that. wiki.content: “Mad Love” is the second single off Mabel’s album, High Expectations. It talks about a sexual relationship between two people. On her YouTube channel, the singer talked about the creative process behind the song-writing in the studio session after the set of artists had written the previous single: I just wanna write something positive that had attitude, but still was sending quite a simple message of just how good it feels when you like somebody and they like you, and sometimes it doesn’t have to be more complicated than that. And we just were trying to think what’s the easiest, simplest […] way we can put this without it being boring, ‘cause sometimes my problem is that I over-think the lyrics, so “Mad Love” for me was a challenge, because sometimes, actually, striping it back can be harder.
